-- Grizzlies Rally to Force Game 7 Against Clippers in NBA Playoffs
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2012-05-12T04:27:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-12/grizzlies-rally-to-force-game-7-against-clippers-in-nba-playoffs.html
Marc Gasol had 23 points for the
Memphis Grizzlies who avoided elimination in the National
Basketball Association’s first-round playoffs with a 90-88
victory over the  Los Angeles Clippers .  The teams meet tomorrow in Memphis for the final game in
their best-of-seven series.  Zach Randolph had 18 points and 16 rebounds for the
Grizzlies last night at Staples Center in Los Angeles.  Blake Griffin scored 17 points and Eric Bledsoe added 14
for the Clippers, who were ahead by eight points with eight
minutes, 30 seconds left in the game. Two minutes later, Rudy Gay scored on a seven-foot running jumper to give the Grizzlies
a 77-76 lead.  The Clippers regained the advantage until Mike Conley’s 3-
pointer with four minutes, 37 seconds left gave the Grizzlies an
83-80 lead.  In tonight’s first-round game, the Denver Nuggets visit the
 Los Angeles Lakers  to break their 3-3 Western Conference series
tie.  In the first game of the Eastern Conference semifinals, the
Boston Celtics host the  Philadelphia 76ers .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at 
